I need the platform's tracking link format
To help you with the tracking link format, could you please specify which tracking platform or service you're using? This will allow me to provide you with the most accurate information.

For integrating Google Analytics with News Break, you can use UTM parameters to track your campaigns. Here's a basic format for the tracking link: 

`https://www.yourwebsite.com/?utm_source=newsbreak&utm_medium=ad&utm_campaign=your_campaign_name`

Make sure to replace `yourwebsite.com` and `your_campaign_name` with your actual website URL and campaign name. If you need more detailed instructions, feel free to ask!
Is it possible to modify the last character to &utm_campaign=campaign_name?

Yes, you can modify the last character to use `&utm_campaign=campaign_name` in your tracking link. Here's how it would look:

`https://www.yourwebsite.com/?utm_source=newsbreak&utm_medium=ad&utm_campaign=campaign_name`

Just ensure that each parameter is separated by an ampersand (`&`) and replace `campaign_name` with your actual campaign name.
Can this tracking link solution track my account ID and campaign name?

Yes, you can include additional parameters in your tracking link to track your account ID and campaign name. Here's an example of how you might structure it:

`https://www.yourwebsite.com/?utm_source=newsbreak&utm_medium=ad&utm_campaign=campaign_name&utm_content=account_id`

Replace `campaign_name` and `account_id` with your actual campaign name and account ID. This way, Google Analytics will capture these details for better tracking.
Why did my ad pass the review but not show for two days?

There could be several reasons why your ad isn't showing even after passing the review. Let's check a few things: 

1. **Campaign Start Date**: Ensure that the campaign start date is set correctly and has already begun.
2. **Bidding Type**: Verify if the bidding type is appropriate for your campaign goals.
3. **Targeting or Budget Settings**: Double-check your targeting settings and budget to ensure they align with your campaign objectives.
4. **Recent Changes**: If you've made any changes in the last 72 hours, it might take some time for those changes to reflect.

If everything seems correct and it's still not showing, I recommend reaching out to our support team at adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance.
